race.comment: Good contest to end the day. SPEEDY HENRY (3) resumed in a solid rating contest with an eye-catching fourth over 1100m at Gosford. Gets map favours today with the tongue-tie going on. Hard to stop from the good gate. NAVY STEEL (2) building a solid winning record and strips fitter after launching late from back in the field when seventh to Massira over 1000m at Randwick in Highway class. Extra trip suits and shapes as the main danger. ANTILOCAPRA (6) returns from a lengthy break after going quickly through her grades last time in. Sent to town when a tough on-pace second over 1400m in Highway class at Rosehill. Back without a trial and ticks a few boxes. MISS CHECKONI (7) tough old mare who will find this easier after bumping into Oui Oui Oui and Aroha Stone from wide gates at her last two outings. Will relish the claim and can surprise at the good each way odds.
